                <span class="fs5"><!-- OldURL: http://boards2.parentsplace.com/messages/get/pplibchristiann9/36.html -->
<p>Lectionary **Study** (Get your butt in here, Luahiwa!) for November 11...</p>

Here are the lessons for next week. As always, please feel welcome to share your ideas and insights on next Sunday's lessons, especially if you can think of some way to share the themes with your children. Or, if you don't have something to contribute to any of the posted questions, you could try posting your own questions.
<P>


<PRE>                   Revised Common Lectionary </PRE>
<P>


<PRE>   Old Testament   Haggai 1:15b-2:9                  
   Psalm           Psalm 145:1-5, 17-21 or Psalm 98
   or
   Old Testament   Job 19:23-27
   Psalm           Psalm 17:1-9
   Epistle         2 Thessalonians 2:1-5, 13-17
   Gospel          Luke 20:27-38</PRE>
<P>


<PRE> RCL: <A HREF="http://divinity.library.vanderbilt.edu/lectionary/CPentecost/cProper27.htm">http://divinity.library.vanderbilt.edu/lectionary/CPentecost/cProper27.htm</A></PRE>
<P>


<PRE>Sunday-school:
 <A HREF="http://www.sundayschoollessons.com/pen23les.htm">http://www.sundayschoollessons.com/pen23les.htm</A>
 <A HREF="http://www.sundayschoollessons.com/pen23art.htm">http://www.sundayschoollessons.com/pen23art.htm</A>
 <A HREF="http://www.sundayschoollessons.com/pen23lart.htm">http://www.sundayschoollessons.com/pen23lart.htm</A></PRE>
<P>


<PRE>Commentary from the Anglican Diocese of Montreal
 <A HREF="http://www.montreal.anglican.org/comment/thisweek.shtml">http://www.montreal.anglican.org/comment/thisweek.shtml</A> </PRE>
