                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">emoticon:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp;<img src="http://acx.prospero.com/dir-app/icon.aspx?realmId=185&iconTypeId=2&iconName=14" border=0 height=15 width=15 align=texttop alt="Emoticon"></span></div></div>
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">message #:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; 771.19 in response to <a href="message.asp?webtag=iv-pplibchrist&msg=771.18" target=_self>771.18</a></span></div></div>


                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">from:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; <a class="memname" href="/dir-app/bbcard/profile.asp?webtag=iv-pplibchrist&uid=369383651" onClick="return LBB(369383651);">pmclean</a> <nobr>&nbsp;<img src="http://acx.prospero.com/dir-app/icon.aspx?realmId=185&iconTypeId=1&iconName=cl" border=0 height=15 width=15 align=texttop alt='Member Icon'></nobr></span></div></div>
                
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">to:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; <a class="memname" href="/dir-app/bbcard/profile.asp?webtag=iv-pplibchrist&uid=369883572" onClick="return LBB(369883572);">cgi_bin</a> <nobr></nobr></span></div></div>
                
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">date:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; 11/9/2001 9:05 pm</span></div></div>
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">replies:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; 20</span></div></div>
            </div><!-- End: mainBodyTextTop -->

            <br clear="all" />

            <div class="mainBodyText">
                <span class="fs5"><!-- OldURL: http://boards2.parentsplace.com/messages/get/pplibchristiann9/36/4/1/1/1.html -->
<p>The most basic resource is an *Oxford* study bible. Its study notes are what Dave calls "scholarly"...</p>

by which he means phenomenological -- that is, providing background and context based on research that uses the scientific model, of seeking external and objective evidence. In contrast, Zondervan, Ryrie, Thompson and Nelson study bibles provide background and context based on ... more bible study -- and much of that bible study relies on traditional interpretations, dogma, and literalism. 
<P>

The notes in a study bible comprise a basic, minimal commentary. You can also acquire more comprehensive commentaries, and sometimes access them on the Internet. See Higgs et al's discussion above on commentaries and Internet above at <A HREF="http://boards2.parentsplace.com/messages/get/pplibchristiann9/24.html">http://boards2.parentsplace.com/messages/get/pplibchristiann9/24.html</A>
<P>

In the case of this Haggai reading, it helps that I've previously read Samuel, Kings, Chronicals, and Ezra; which document from a biblical perspective the events leading up to Haggai's prophecy. I also studied with dear Dr. Craigie for a little while: <A HREF="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/066421813X/qid=1005363915/sr=1-2/ref=sr_1_10_2/102-7623950-3415360">http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/066421813X/qid=1005363915/sr=1-2/ref=sr_1_10_2/102-7623950-3415360</A>. Alas, I presently have only volume 1 of this work, but I'm heading down to Augsburg Fortress as soon as I get 15 minutes of freedom during shop hours, to see if I can find this volume.

<P>

</span>
                <table><tr></tr></table>
