            <br clear="all" />

            <div class="mainBodyText">
                <span class="fs5"><!-- OldURL: http://boards2.parentsplace.com/messages/get/pplibchristiann9/36/4/1/1/1/1.html -->
<p>I have a great Oxford Annotated w/Apocrypha (hardback) on my shelf, along with several Zondervans</p>

...and I see the difference in the lens in which these books are annotated. For "religious" bibles, Zondervan seems to be the most open-minded; I had a Nelson or two (women's bibles) that I gave away because the lens just couldn't grab me at all. I felt dumber and dumber for every page I turned, and then I got madder and madder at the "you can't use no head knowledge to understand the Lord's good graces; you need heart knowledge". Well isn't that special.
<P>

But my Oxford sure is awesome. 

<P>

</span>
